cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with image retrieval using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of hard positive and hard negative examples and the proposed trainable Generalized-Mean (GeM) pooling layer involve machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The reconstruction of 3D models and the use of structure-from-motion methods involve computer graphics (cs.MM). Finally, the fully automatic fine-tuning of CNNs without human annotation involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
